{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_eae6f7eeb2bc49a98e5fb21b","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Phase 2 User Routes — Task Reference\n2\t\n3\t## Global Rules\n4\t- Working directory: `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment`\n5\t- These tasks depend on Task 2.1 (TTCPortalUser) being complete\n6\t- All routes require authentication via `requireAuth()` from `app/utils/auth-middleware.ts`\n7\t- Do NOT modify `app/utils/auth.ts` or `app/utils/ttc-portal-user.ts`\n8\t- Match legacy response format exactly (JSON responses via `Response.json()`)\n9\t\n10\t## Loop\n11\t- Implement: read this file, do Task N. Run `npx tsc --noEmit`. Commit.\n12\t- Review: read this file, check Task N. Fix or say \"all clean.\"\n13\t- Max 3 review rounds per task.\n14\t\n15\t---\n16\t\n17\t## Task 1: Wire Form Persistence in Upload Endpoint\n18\t\n19\t- Slug: `wire-upload`\n20\t- Goal: Replace the \"intentionally deferred\" comment in upload-form-data with real GCS persistence.\n21\t\n22\t### Read These Files First\n23\t1. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/users/upload-form-data/route.ts` (full file, ~317 lines) — the file to modify. Focus on lines 304-307 where it says \"Form data persistence is intentionally deferred.\"\n24\t2. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/utils/ttc-portal-user.ts` — the class to use for persistence\n25\t3. `/Users/m/Downloads/europe-ttp-master@44c225683f8/ttc_portal_user.py` (lines 403-424) — legacy `UsersService.post()` showing the upload flow\n26\t\n27\t### Changes Required\n28\t\n29\t**Modify `app/users/upload-form-data/route.ts`:**\n30\t\n31\tAdd import at top (note: upload-form-data is at `app/users/upload-form-data/`, so `app/utils/` is two levels up):\n32\t```typescript\n33\timport { TTCPortalUser } from '../../utils/ttc-portal-user';\n34\t```\n35\t\n36\tReplace lines 304-307 (the deferred comment + return) with:\n37\t```typescript\n38\t  // 5. Persist form data to GCS\n39\t  const formUser = await TTCPortalUser.create(user);\n40\t  formUser.setHomeCountry(\n41\t    validation.data!.user_home_country_iso\n42\t    || request.headers.get('x-appengine-country')\n43\t    || request.headers.get('x-vercel-ip-country')\n44\t    || ''\n45\t  );\n46\t\n47\t  // form_data / form_instance_page_data arrive as JSON strings from form-urlencoded\n48\t  // but as objects from JSON callers. Parse only if string.\n49\t  const formData = typeof validation.data!.form_data === 'string'\n50\t    ? JSON.parse(validation.data!.form_data) : validation.data!.form_data;\n51\t  const pageData = typeof validation.data!.form_instance_page_data === 'string'\n52\t    ? JSON.parse(validation.data!.form_instance_page_data) : validation.data!.form_instance_page_data;\n53\t\n54\t  formUser.setFormData(\n55\t    validation.data!.form_type!,\n56\t    validation.data!.form_instance || '',\n57\t    formData,\n58\t    pageData,\n59\t    validation.data!.form_instance_display || ''\n60\t  );\n61\t  await formUser.saveUserData();\n62\t\n63\t  return Response.json(\n64\t    {\n65\t      ok: true,\n66\t      user: user,\n67\t    },\n68\t    { status: 200 }\n69\t  );\n70\t```\n71\t\n72\t### Verification\n73\t- `npx tsc --noEmit` must pass\n74\t- Commit message: `feat: wire form data persistence to GCS in upload endpoint`\n75\t\n76\t---\n77\t\n78\t## Task 2: Create User Data Routes\n79\t\n80\t- Slug: `user-data-routes`\n81\t- Goal: Create 4 user-facing API routes matching legacy `/users/*` endpoints.\n82\t\n83\t### Read These Files First\n84\t1. `/Users/m/Downloads/europe-ttp-master@44c225683f8/ttc_portal_user.py` (lines 426-462) — `UsersService.get()` showing all route handlers\n85\t2. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/utils/ttc-portal-user.ts` — the class to use\n86\t3. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/utils/auth-middleware.ts` — `requireAuth()` function\n87\t4. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/users/upload-form-data/route.ts` (lines 1-30) — import style pattern for user routes\n88\t\n89\t### Changes Required\n90\t\n91\t**Create `app/users/get-form-data/route.ts`:**\n92\t```typescript\n93\timport { requireAuth } from '../../utils/auth-middleware';\n94\timport { TTCPortalUser } from '../../utils/ttc-portal-user';\n95\t\n96\texport async function GET(request: Request): Promise<Response> {\n97\t  const auth = await requireAuth(request);\n98\t  if (auth instanceof Response) return auth;\n99\t\n100\t  const url = new URL(request.url);\n101\t  const formType = url.searchParams.get('form_type') || '';\n102\t  const formInstance = url.searchParams.get('form_instance') || '';\n103\t\n104\t  const user = await TTCPortalUser.create(auth.email);\n105\t  const data = user.getFormData(formType, formInstance);\n106\t  return Response.json(data);\n107\t}\n108\t```\n109\t\n110\t**Create `app/users/get-form-instances/route.ts`:**\n111\tSame pattern. Reads `form_type` from query params. Returns `user.getFormInstances(formType)`.\n112\t\n113\t**Create `app/users/set-config/route.ts`:**\n114\tPOST handler. Reads body (`{ config_params: {...} }`). Legacy uses jQuery `$.post()` which sends form-urlencoded by default, but also supports JSON. Handle both content types:\n115\t```typescript\n116\texport async function POST(request: Request): Promise<Response> {\n117\t  const auth = await requireAuth(request);\n118\t  if (auth instanceof Response) return auth;\n119\t\n120\t  const contentType = request.headers.get('content-type') || '';\n121\t  let body: { config_params?: Record<string, unknown> };\n122\t  \n123\t  if (contentType.includes('application/json')) {\n124\t    body = await request.json();\n125\t  } else {\n126\t    const formData = await request.formData();\n127\t    const configParamsStr = formData.get('config_params');\n128\t    body = {\n129\t      config_params: typeof configParamsStr === 'string'\n130\t        ? JSON.parse(configParamsStr)\n131\t        : configParamsStr,\n132\t    };\n133\t  }\n134\t\n135\t  const user = await TTCPortalUser.create(auth.email);\n136\t  user.setConfig(body.config_params || {});\n137\t  await user.saveUserData();\n138\t  \n139\t  return Response.json({ ok: true });\n140\t}\n141\t```\n142\t\n143\t**Create `app/users/get-config/route.ts`:**\n144\tGET handler. Returns `Response.json(user.getConfig())`.\n145\t\n146\t### Constraints\n147\t- All routes use `requireAuth()` — these are user-facing, not admin\n148\t- Match legacy query param names exactly: `form_type`, `form_instance`, `config_params`\n149\t- Do NOT add admin-only check — any authenticated user can access their own data\n150\t\n151\t### Verification\n152\t- `npx tsc --noEmit` must pass\n153\t- Commit message: `feat: add user data routes for form-data, instances, and config`\n154\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c6988720-3697-4284-939e-7b452fa9fd64","uuid":"2cf5d192-7ea8-44b2-a0f0-f5c5e84a7b25","timestamp":"2026-04-06T10:38:40.296Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/.agent/tasks/task-2-user-routes.md","content":"# Phase 2 User Routes — Task Reference\n\n## Global Rules\n- Working directory: `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment`\n- These tasks depend on Task 2.1 (TTCPortalUser) being complete\n- All routes require authentication via `requireAuth()` from `app/utils/auth-middleware.ts`\n- Do NOT modify `app/utils/auth.ts` or `app/utils/ttc-portal-user.ts`\n- Match legacy response format exactly (JSON responses via `Response.json()`)\n\n## Loop\n- Implement: read this file, do Task N. Run `npx tsc --noEmit`. Commit.\n- Review: read this file, check Task N. Fix or say \"all clean.\"\n- Max 3 review rounds per task.\n\n---\n\n## Task 1: Wire Form Persistence in Upload Endpoint\n\n- Slug: `wire-upload`\n- Goal: Replace the \"intentionally deferred\" comment in upload-form-data with real GCS persistence.\n\n### Read These Files First\n1. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/users/upload-form-data/route.ts` (full file, ~317 lines) — the file to modify. Focus on lines 304-307 where it says \"Form data persistence is intentionally deferred.\"\n2. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/utils/ttc-portal-user.ts` — the class to use for persistence\n3. `/Users/m/Downloads/europe-ttp-master@44c225683f8/ttc_portal_user.py` (lines 403-424) — legacy `UsersService.post()` showing the upload flow\n\n### Changes Required\n\n**Modify `app/users/upload-form-data/route.ts`:**\n\nAdd import at top (note: upload-form-data is at `app/users/upload-form-data/`, so `app/utils/` is two levels up):\n```typescript\nimport { TTCPortalUser } from '../../utils/ttc-portal-user';\n```\n\nReplace lines 304-307 (the deferred comment + return) with:\n```typescript\n  // 5. Persist form data to GCS\n  const formUser = await TTCPortalUser.create(user);\n  formUser.setHomeCountry(\n    validation.data!.user_home_country_iso\n    || request.headers.get('x-appengine-country')\n    || request.headers.get('x-vercel-ip-country')\n    || ''\n  );\n\n  // form_data / form_instance_page_data arrive as JSON strings from form-urlencoded\n  // but as objects from JSON callers. Parse only if string.\n  const formData = typeof validation.data!.form_data === 'string'\n    ? JSON.parse(validation.data!.form_data) : validation.data!.form_data;\n  const pageData = typeof validation.data!.form_instance_page_data === 'string'\n    ? JSON.parse(validation.data!.form_instance_page_data) : validation.data!.form_instance_page_data;\n\n  formUser.setFormData(\n    validation.data!.form_type!,\n    validation.data!.form_instance || '',\n    formData,\n    pageData,\n    validation.data!.form_instance_display || ''\n  );\n  await formUser.saveUserData();\n\n  return Response.json(\n    {\n      ok: true,\n      user: user,\n    },\n    { status: 200 }\n  );\n```\n\n### Verification\n- `npx tsc --noEmit` must pass\n- Commit message: `feat: wire form data persistence to GCS in upload endpoint`\n\n---\n\n## Task 2: Create User Data Routes\n\n- Slug: `user-data-routes`\n- Goal: Create 4 user-facing API routes matching legacy `/users/*` endpoints.\n\n### Read These Files First\n1. `/Users/m/Downloads/europe-ttp-master@44c225683f8/ttc_portal_user.py` (lines 426-462) — `UsersService.get()` showing all route handlers\n2. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/utils/ttc-portal-user.ts` — the class to use\n3. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/utils/auth-middleware.ts` — `requireAuth()` function\n4. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/users/upload-form-data/route.ts` (lines 1-30) — import style pattern for user routes\n\n### Changes Required\n\n**Create `app/users/get-form-data/route.ts`:**\n```typescript\nimport { requireAuth } from '../../utils/auth-middleware';\nimport { TTCPortalUser } from '../../utils/ttc-portal-user';\n\nexport async function GET(request: Request): Promise<Response> {\n  const auth = await requireAuth(request);\n  if (auth instanceof Response) return auth;\n\n  const url = new URL(request.url);\n  const formType = url.searchParams.get('form_type') || '';\n  const formInstance = url.searchParams.get('form_instance') || '';\n\n  const user = await TTCPortalUser.create(auth.email);\n  const data = user.getFormData(formType, formInstance);\n  return Response.json(data);\n}\n```\n\n**Create `app/users/get-form-instances/route.ts`:**\nSame pattern. Reads `form_type` from query params. Returns `user.getFormInstances(formType)`.\n\n**Create `app/users/set-config/route.ts`:**\nPOST handler. Reads body (`{ config_params: {...} }`). Legacy uses jQuery `$.post()` which sends form-urlencoded by default, but also supports JSON. Handle both content types:\n```typescript\nexport async function POST(request: Request): Promise<Response> {\n  const auth = await requireAuth(request);\n  if (auth instanceof Response) return auth;\n\n  const contentType = request.headers.get('content-type') || '';\n  let body: { config_params?: Record<string, unknown> };\n  \n  if (contentType.includes('application/json')) {\n    body = await request.json();\n  } else {\n    const formData = await request.formData();\n    const configParamsStr = formData.get('config_params');\n    body = {\n      config_params: typeof configParamsStr === 'string'\n        ? JSON.parse(configParamsStr)\n        : configParamsStr,\n    };\n  }\n\n  const user = await TTCPortalUser.create(auth.email);\n  user.setConfig(body.config_params || {});\n  await user.saveUserData();\n  \n  return Response.json({ ok: true });\n}\n```\n\n**Create `app/users/get-config/route.ts`:**\nGET handler. Returns `Response.json(user.getConfig())`.\n\n### Constraints\n- All routes use `requireAuth()` — these are user-facing, not admin\n- Match legacy query param names exactly: `form_type`, `form_instance`, `config_params`\n- Do NOT add admin-only check — any authenticated user can access their own data\n\n### Verification\n- `npx tsc --noEmit` must pass\n- Commit message: `feat: add user data routes for form-data, instances, and config`\n","numLines":154,"startLine":1,"totalLines":154}}}
